sentences.sentence:
Terania and ARE will use their best endeavours to ensure that the Compliance Programme is designed and implemented so as to comply with each of the following requirements:


 2.1 the Compliance Programme is to cover all officers, employees, representatives and agents of Terania and ARE who perform duties in Australia;
 2.2 the Compliance Programme is to inform the officers, employees, representatives and agents of Terania and ARE who perform duties in Australia of the application of Division 1 of Part V ("the relevant provisions of the Act") of the Trade Practices Act ("TPA") to the business of Terania and ARE;
 2.3 the Compliance Programme must require the appointment of a senior officer ("the Compliance Officer"), within 3 months of commencing trading activities, whose responsibilities are to include the maintenance and continuing implementation of the Compliance Programme and who reports directly to the company board or governing body;
 2.4 Terania and ARE shall appoint a qualified, internal or external compliance professional with expertise in trade practices issues ("the Compliance Advisor") within 3 months of commencing trading activities for the purpose as set out in paragraph 2.5;
 2.5 Terania and ARE shall instruct the Compliance Advisor to conduct a TPA risk assessment ("the risk assessment") in accordance with the following: 




 2.5.1 identify the areas where Terania and ARE are at risk of breaching Division 1 of Part V of the TPA;
 2.5.2 assess the likelihood of these risks occurring and the consequences of the risks to the business operations of Terania and ARE, should they occur;
 2.5.3 identify where there may be gaps in Terania's and ARE's existing procedures for managing these risks; and 




 2.5.4 provide recommendations for action having regard to the assessment;
 2.6 the Compliance Programme is to require officers, employees, representatives and agents of Terania and ARE to confidentially notify the Compliance Officer of potential breaches of the relevant provisions of the TPA and the Compliance Programme by Terania and ARE;
 2.7 the Compliance Programme is to include a complaints handling system that is consistent with Australian Standard AS4269-1995;
 2.8 the Compliance Programme must require the Compliance Officer to keep and maintain a register of potential breaches and/or complaints related to the relevant provisions of the TPA;
 2.9 the Compliance Programme must require the development of a disciplinary policy or code for those employees and agents who do not comply with the Compliance Programme or the relevant provisions of the TPA;
 2.10 the Compliance Programme must require that compliance with the Compliance Programme and the relevant provisions of the TPA is a key performance indicator for all employees;
 2.11 the Compliance Programme is to provide for the conducting of regular trade practices training (at least once a year) by an internal designated compliance trainer (who has been trained by a solicitor or compliance professional with expertise in trade practices law) and/or a solicitor or compliance professional with expertise in trade practices law for all officers, employees, representatives and agents of Terania and ARE; and
 2.12 the Compliance Programme is to provide for an induction programme on trade practices compliance issues to be undertaken by all new officers, employees, representatives and agents of Terania and ARE within 3 months of his or her engagement.

The reviewer will qualify as independent on the basis that he or she: 




 4.1.1 is not a present or past staff member or director of Terania and/or ARE:
 4.1.2 has not acted or does not act for Terania and/or ARE other than reviewing the Compliance Programme of Terania and/or ARE;
 4.1.3 is not retained by Terania and/or ARE in any other capacity, either currently or in the past other than in the capacity of being engaged to review the Compliance Programme of Terania and/or ARE;
 4.1.4 has not and does not provide consultancy or other services for Terania and/or ARE other than reviewing the Compliance Programme of Terania and/or ARE; 




 4.1.5 has no shareholding or other interests in Terania and/or ARE; and
 4.1.6 is not the Compliance Advisor appointed pursuant to paragraph 2.4; 


4.2 Terania and ARE shall use its best endeavours to ensure that the reviewer:



 4.2.1 conducts a critical review as to whether the Compliance Programme has been implemented in compliance with each of the requirements of the order in paragraph 4; and
 4.2.2 makes such recommendations as he/she considers necessary to ensure that the Compliance Programme complies with each of the requirements of the order in paragraph 4; 




 4.3 Terania and ARE shall ensure that the review is able to be conducted by the reviewer on the basis of any relevant information in Terania and/or ARE's possession or control, including without limitation any of the following sources of information: 




 4.3.1 investigations of any officer, employees, representatives and agents of Terania and/or ARE to find out how compliance processes are implemented and understood;
 4.3.2 enquiries of customers about their experience of Terania and/or ARE and its products/services;
 4.3.3 Terania's and/or ARE's records, including its complaints register and any documents relevant to its training or induction programme; and
 4.3.4 documents created by Terania's and/or ARE's consultants and solicitors for use in Terania's and/or ARE's Compliance Programme; 




 4.4 Terania and ARE shall use their best endeavours to ensure that a review is completed one year after the Compliance Programme is established, and at the conclusion of each period of 12 months during which the Compliance Programme is being maintained and implemented;
 4.5 Terania and ARE shall use their best endeavours to ensure that the reviewer sets out the findings of the review in a written report ("the review report") and provided to Terania and ARE within 14 days of the completion of the review.
